This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user's goal throughout this session is to achieve comprehensive test coverage for a Next.js + MariaDB football league management system. The session progressed through:
   - Auditing which source files have no tests at all (beyond what the codecov report shows)
   - Adding test scaffolding (it.todo) for all genuinely untested files
   - Implementing real tests for the invoice page (replacing todos)
   - Expanding the coverage config to actually measure the newly tested files
   - Discussing and approving a refactor to make `src/actions/` vs `src/lib/actions/` architecturally consistent
   - The most recent approval: "Yes, go ahead" to execute three specific refactors

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Vitest with multiple config files (`vitest.unit.config.ts` as aggregate, plus `vitest.actions.config.ts`, `vitest.lib.config.ts`, `vitest.pages.config.ts`, etc.)
   - Coverage `include`/`exclude` in vitest unit config determines what appears in the codecov report
   - `src/actions/*.ts` — "use server" boundary files (auth guard + call lib core + revalidate + broadcast)
   - `src/lib/actions/*/` — pure business logic cores, testable without Next.js mocking
   - Manual mocks in `__mocks__/index.ts` sibling to service directories
   - `vi.hoisted()` pattern for setting up mocks before imports in Vitest
   - `vi.mock('services/GameDay')` uses alias from vitest.pages.config.ts (not `@/services/GameDay`)
   - `findElement` JSX tree walker pattern used in page tests to inspect React element props without rendering
   - `vi.useFakeTimers()` / `vi.setSystemTime()` for date-sensitive tests

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`vitest.unit.config.ts`** — Updated to expand coverage scope:
     ```ts
     coverage: {
         include: [
             'src/actions/**/*.{ts,tsx}',         // NEW — outer action wrappers
             'src/app/api/**/*.{ts,tsx}',
             'src/app/footy/**/*.{ts,tsx}',        // NEW — pages
             'src/components/**/*.{ts,tsx}',
             'src/lib/**/*.{ts,tsx}',              // NEW — broader than just lib/actions
             'src/services/**/*.{ts,tsx}',
         ],
         exclude: [
             '**/__mocks__/**',
             '**/*.stories.*',
             '**/*.vitest.spec.ts',
             '**/*.vitest.spec.tsx',
             '**/*.test.ts',
             '**/*.test.tsx',
             '**/*Skeleton*',
             '**/index.ts',
             '**/prisma/**',
             '.storybook/**',
             'public/**',
             // 'src/actions/**' REMOVED — was previously explicitly excluded
             'src/app/api/auth/**',
             'src/app/footy/docs/**',              // NEW — MDX-only pages
             'src/lib/importlivedb/**',            // NEW — dev-only utility
             'src/stories/**',
             'src/tests/**',
             'src/types/**',
         ],
         reporter: ['text', 'lcov', 'cobertura'],
         reportsDirectory: 'coverage',
     },
     ```

   - **`src/services/GameDay/__mocks__/index.ts`** — Added 16 missing mock methods:
     ```ts
     import { vi } from 'vitest';
