   - **`src/lib/prismaErrors.vitest.spec.ts`** — Scaffolding with 1 live test (P2025 error) + 4 todos

   - **Action wrapper scaffolding files** (all in `src/lib/actions/*/`, all todos):
     - `authAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `authExportAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - `createMoreGameDaysAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `createPlayerAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - `deletePlayerAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `recordHallHireAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - `sendEmailToAllActivePlayersAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `setGameEnabledAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - `submitGameInvitationResponseAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `submitPickerAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - `submitResponseAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `triggerInvitationsAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - `updatePlayerAction.vitest.spec.ts`, `updatePlayerRecordsAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - **New directories created**: `src/lib/actions/getProgress/getProgressAction.vitest.spec.ts`
     - **New directories created**: `src/lib/actions/updateInvoiceGameDays/updateInvoiceGameDaysAction.vitest.spec.ts`

   - **`src/actions/setDrinkers.ts`** — PENDING REFACTOR. Currently contains:
     ```ts
     export async function setDrinkers(rawData: unknown) {
         await requireAdmin();
         const data = SetDrinkersInputSchema.parse(rawData);
         const result = await setDrinkersCore(data);
         try {
             await playerRecordService.upsertFromGameDay(data.gameDayId);
         } catch (error) {
             const normalizedError = normalizeUnknownError(error);
             throw new InternalError(`Failed to update player records for game day ${data.gameDayId}.`, {
                 cause: normalizedError,
                 details: { gameDayId: data.gameDayId, operation: 'upsertFromGameDay', upstreamCode: normalizedError.code },
                 publicMessage: 'Failed to update player records.',
             });
         }
         revalidatePath('/footy/admin/drinkers');
         revalidatePath(`/footy/admin/drinkers/${data.gameDayId}`);
         revalidatePath('/footy/pub');
         revalidatePath('/footy/table/pub');
         revalidatePath(`/footy/game/${data.gameDayId}`);
         broadcast(FootyChannel.Games);
         return result;
     }
     ```
     The upsertFromGameDay + error handling block should move to the lib core.

   - **`src/actions/setGameResult.ts`** — PENDING REFACTOR. Identical upsertFromGameDay + error handling pattern as setDrinkers, should move to lib core.

   - **`src/actions/updateInvoiceGameDays.ts`** — PENDING REFACTOR. Has actual business logic (Zod parse + Promise.all over service updates) with no lib counterpart:
     ```ts
     export async function updateInvoiceGameDays(rawData: unknown) {
         await requireAdmin();
         const data = UpdateInvoiceGameDaysInputSchema.parse(rawData);
         await Promise.all(
             data.gameDays.map((gd) => gameDayService.update({ id: gd.id, game: gd.gameScheduled })),
         );
         revalidatePath('/footy/admin/invoice');
         revalidatePath('/footy/fixtures');
         broadcast([FootyChannel.Money, FootyChannel.Games]);
     }
     ```

4. Errors and Fixes:
   - **`gameDayService.getForMonth` undefined error**: When running invoice page tests, `(gameDayService.getForMonth as Mock).mockResolvedValue([])` threw `Cannot read properties of undefined`. Cause: the manual mock at `src/services/GameDay/__mocks__/index.ts` only had 7 methods and was missing `getForMonth`. Fix: Added all 16 missing methods to the mock file.

5. Problem Solving:
   - Correctly identified that `src/lib/dates.vitest.spec.ts` was actually testing `bankHolidays.ts` (misleading filename — only imports from bankHolidays)
   - Correctly identified that `vi.mock('services/GameDay')` uses the `services` alias (resolves to `src/services/`) not `@/services/GameDay`
   - Confirmed that page tests don't need to mock component imports — React elements in the JSX tree are inspectable via `findElement` without rendering
   - Identified that the thin redirect pages (fixtures, results) have no logic worth testing, while invoice page does
   - Diagnosed why coverage stats didn't move: the vitest.unit.config.ts coverage scope was too narrow

6. All user messages:
